const price = 29.99;
const discount = price * 0.20;
const finalPrice = price - discount;
console.log(`Original: €${price} | Discounted: €${finalPrice.toFixed(2)}`);
```

The key insight: `.toFixed(2)` formats floating-point math (which is never perfectly clean) to exactly 2 decimal places.

